public abstract class ZFSObject
extends java.lang.Object

Represents ZFS snapshot, file system, volume, or pool.

createSnapshot

public ZFSSnapshot createSnapshot(java.lang.String snapshotName,
                                  boolean recursive)
Take a snapshot of this ZFS dataset and recursively for all child datasets.

Parameters:
snapshotName - the name of the Snapshot to create, i.e. 'monday', 'before-test'.
recursive - should snapshot recursively create snapshot for all descendant datasets. Snapshots are taken atomically, so that all recursive snapshots correspond to the same moment in time.
Returns:
the created snapshot of this dataset.

destory

public void destory()
Wipes out the dataset and all its data. Very dangerous.

If this dataset contains nested datasets, this method fails with ErrorCode.EZFS_EXISTS.
